="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig05a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig05b.jpeg" height="1359" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig05b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig06a.jpeg" height="1150" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig06a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig06b.jpeg" height="1180" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig06b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig06c.jpeg" height="1443" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig06c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig07.jpeg" height="528" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig07" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7</span> Cannula malposition in a 74-year-old man with suboptimal LVAD flow and decreased urine output on postoperative day 2. Owing to concern about possible kinking of the inflow cannula, the patient was returned to the operating room. Image from intraoperative transesophageal echocardiography shows random cessation of flow (white arrows) and variable flow velocity during ventricular systole without varying R-R intervals (black arrows). These findings suggest abutment of the inflow cannula against a ventricular wall. Cannula malposition was confirmed at surgery, and the cannula was realigned.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig07">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig08.jpeg" height="811" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig08" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8</span> Tearing of the outflow cannula attachment to the aorta in a 57-year-old man who underwent high- risk coronary revascularization for ischemic cardiomy-opathy. On postoperative day 1, ventricular fibrillation and cardiac arrest developed, which necessitated LVAD implantation for cardiac support. On postoperative day 16, the patient was cyanotic and unresponsive. Resus-citation was attempted but was unsuccessful. Autopsy photograph shows a tear (black arrow) at the attachment between the outflow cannula (white arrow) and the ascending aorta <i>(Ao)</i>; in addition, 750 mL of blood was found within the pericardium. Two coronary artery bypass grafts (arrowheads) are also attached to the aorta.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig08">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig09.jpeg" height="1422" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> Postoperative hemorrhage in a 50-year-old man in whom hypotension and intermittent ventricular tachycardia developed 9 days after implantation of a VentrAssist LVAD. Axial image from ECG-gated 64–detector row dual-source CT shows a large circumferential pericardial hemorrhagic effusion (arrow). The hemorrhage resolved without intervention. The outflow cannula can be seen in cross section (arrowhead) near the right atrioventricular groove.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig10a.jpeg" height="1620" width="1620" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig10b.jpeg" height="1226" width="1638" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig10c.jpeg" height="1361" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig10c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig11a.jpeg" height="1260" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig11b.jpeg" height="1519" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.302095734&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.302095734/asset/images/095734fig12a.jpeg" height="1285" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12a</span> <!-- There is no content. -->